
[1]punctual

   PUNC'TUAL, a. [L. punctum, a point.]

   1. Consisting in a point; as this punctual spot. [Little used.]

   2. Exact; observant of nice points; punctilious, particularly in
   observing time, appointments or promises. It is honorable in a man to
   be punctual to appointments, or to appointed hours; it is just to be
   punctual in paying debts.

   3. Exact; as a punctual correspondence between a prediction and an
   event.

   4. Done at the exact time; as punctual payment.
